{
  "design_notes": "S0 introduces spacious, atmospheric pad sounds using long, 4-beat sustained holds at key phrases (beats 0, 8, 16) with light, single taps in alternating lanes. This gets players flowing without visual clutter. S1 drives the drop with kick-centric center hits and alternating outer lane snares. To make the melody feel alive, runs rise (GAP -> BAR -> NOTE) and fall (NOTE -> BAR -> GAP) cleanly on integer beats, perfectly respecting the casual subdivision. S2 bridges into the outro with a 4-beat hold representing the fading synth pad decay, resolving on a final tap at beat 64 to resolve the abrupt cut-off issue.",
  "sections": [
